{
  "text": "The rule means that if there is some instance of \"Son\", which belongs to class \"Son\" then this instance has relation \"hasParent\" to class \"Father\". This happens when two concepts are defined and one of them is the part of the other [CITATION_1] . For example, the class \"Heart\" is part of the class \"Organism\". It is possible to generate the following rules [CITATION_2] :",
